  "levelDesignRules": [
    "Render order starts with BG Color, then Water Foam, then the first Flat Ground layer.",
    "For each elevation level, repeat Shadow then Elevated Ground.",
    "Shadow is a 128x128 sprite placed on the same 64x64 grid and shifted one tile downward under elevated walkable area.",
    "Stairs are walkable transition tiles; they connect lower terrain to elevated terrain and should not use a blocking collider.",
    "Cliff art communicates height. Do not use the entire cliff visual layer as the only movement collider, because it can block valid stair exits.",
    "Use different terrain color atlases per elevation level when possible so players can read height changes.",
    "Water Foam belongs wherever terrain touches BG Color/water. Randomize animation start frame for repeated foam tiles."
  ]
